{
  "schema_version": "1.6.2",
  "id": "BIT-pillow-2026-59204",
  "summary": "Pillow JPEG2000 tiled decode retains a growing scratch buffer and can be used for denial of service",
  "details": "Pillow is a Python imaging library. From 8.2.0 through 12.2.0, src/libImaging/Jpeg2KDecode.c accumulates total_component_width across every tile in a JPEG2000 image instead of recomputing it per tile, allowing a crafted tiled JPEG2000 file to force substantially higher transient memory usage and trigger out-of-memory failures during decoding. This issue is fixed in version 12.3.0.",
